dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Breaklines for Buffalo County, WI 2016
dc_description_s: This data represents LiDAR-derived breaklines in Buffalo County, Wisconsin in 2016. Hydro breaklines maintain the definition of water-related features in an elevation model. They are used to capture linear discontinuities in the surface, lake shorelines, single-line drains for small rivers, and double-line drains for large rivers.
uw_supplemental_s: This data is also available as a series of tiles to enable downloads of smaller, more specific areas within the county. To access the tiled data, please visit: https://www.sco.wisc.edu/scoapps/lidar/tile-search/?layer=buffalo
